Origen: Some enzymes in this group hydrolyse alpha-L-arabinosides; some animal enzymes also hydrolyse beta-D-fucosides and beta-D-glucosides; cf. EC 3.2.1.108 lactase.

column1: A P-type ATPase that undergoes covalent phosphorylation during the transport cycle. This enzyme occurs in protozoa, fungi and plants, and generates an electrochemical potential gradient of protons across the plasma membrane.

Origen: EC 3.4.11.5 created 1965 as EC 3.4.1.4, transferred 1972 to EC 3.4.11.5
